    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for 10 of 13 factors; 3 factors (Discretization error, Output comparison, Model form) achieve Gradation 3 against a required Gradation 4, but the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification envelope demonstrates that 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below the clinical threshold of 0.005 g/100 L across all operating points. The credibility team accepts the residual gaps as bounded and the overall evidence package as sufficient for regulatory submission under MRL 5 with documented limitations.",
